WEBVTT

00:15.460 --> 00:25.960
52. Awake, awake, put on thy strength, O Zion, put on thy beautiful garments, O Jerusalem,

00:27.440 --> 00:34.160
for henceforth there shall no more come into thee the uncircumcised and the unclean. Shake

00:34.160 --> 00:40.480
thyself from the dust, arise and sit down, O Jerusalem, loose thyself from the bands of

00:40.480 --> 00:47.600
thy knack, O captive daughter of Zion. For thus saith the Lord, ye have sold yourselves for not,

00:47.860 --> 00:54.500
and ye shall be redeemed without money. For thus saith the Lord God, My people went down a four

00:54.500 --> 01:01.800
time into Egypt to sojourn there, and the Assyrian oppressed them without cause. Now therefore what

01:01.800 --> 01:08.280
have I here, saith the Lord, that My people is taken away for not? They that rule over them

01:08.280 --> 01:15.460
make them to howl, saith the Lord, and My name continually every day is blasphemed. Therefore

01:15.460 --> 01:21.560
My people shall know My name, therefore they shall know in that day that I am He that doth

01:21.560 --> 01:29.080
speak, behold it is I. How beautiful upon the mountains are the feet of Him that bringeth good

01:29.080 --> 01:35.400
tidings, that publisheth peace, that bringeth good tidings of good, that publisheth salvation,

01:36.060 --> 01:43.100
that saith unto Zion, Thy God reigneth. Thy watchmen shall lift up the voice, with the voice

01:43.100 --> 01:49.680
together shall they sing, for they shall see eye to eye when the Lord shall bring again Zion.

01:50.340 --> 01:57.200
Break forth into joy, sing together ye waste places of Jerusalem, for the Lord hath comforted

01:57.200 --> 02:04.500
His people, He hath redeemed Jerusalem. The Lord hath made bare His holy arm in the eyes of all

02:04.500 --> 02:12.040
the nations, and all the ends of the earth shall see the salvation of our God. Depart ye, depart ye,

02:12.160 --> 02:19.080
go ye out from thence, touch no unclean thing, go ye out of the midst of her, be ye clean,

02:19.080 --> 02:26.120
that bear the vessels of the Lord. For ye shall not go out with haste, nor go by flight, for the

02:26.120 --> 02:33.380
Lord will go before you, and the God of Israel will be your reward. Behold, My servant shall deal

02:33.380 --> 02:40.680
prudently, he shall be exalted and extolled and be very high. As many were astonied at thee,

02:41.020 --> 02:47.900
His visage was so marred more than any man, and His form more than the sons of men. So shall

02:47.900 --> 02:54.180
He sprinkle many nations, the kings shall shut their mouths at Him, for that which had not been

02:54.180 --> 02:59.600
told them shall they see, and that which they had not heard shall they consider.

03:01.140 --> 03:07.840
Chapter 53 Who hath believed our report, and to whom is the arm of the Lord revealed? For

03:07.840 --> 03:14.260
He shall grow up before Him as a tender plant, and as a root out of a dry ground. He hath no

03:14.260 --> 03:20.800
form nor comeliness, and when we shall see Him there is no beauty that we should desire Him.

03:21.280 --> 03:28.220
He is despised and rejected of men, a man of sorrows and acquainted with grief, and we hid,

03:28.280 --> 03:36.540
as it were, our faces from Him. He was despised and we esteemed Him not. Surely He hath borne our

03:36.540 --> 03:43.100
griefs and carried our sorrows, yet we did esteem Him stricken, smitten of God and afflicted.

03:43.100 --> 03:50.540
But He was wounded for our transgressions, He was bruised for our iniquities, the chastisement

03:50.540 --> 03:58.280
of our peace was upon Him, and with His stripes we are healed. All we, like sheep, have gone astray,

03:58.520 --> 04:04.880
we have turned every one to His own way, and the Lord hath laid on Him the iniquity of us all.

04:05.240 --> 04:12.040
He was oppressed, and He was afflicted, yet He opened not His mouth. He is brought as a lamb

04:12.040 --> 04:18.280
to the slaughter, and as a sheep before her shearers is dumb, so He openeth not His mouth.

04:18.860 --> 04:25.820
He was taken from prison and from judgment, and who shall declare His generation? For He was cut

04:25.820 --> 04:31.240
off out of the land of the living, for the transgression of My people was He stricken.

04:31.920 --> 04:37.740
And He made His grave with the wicked and with the rich in His death, because He had done no

04:37.740 --> 04:44.640
violence, neither was any deceit in His mouth. Yet it pleased the Lord to bruise Him, He hath put

04:44.640 --> 04:50.820
Him to grief. When Thou shalt make His soul an offering for sin, He shall see His seed,

04:51.000 --> 04:57.380
He shall prolong His days, and the pleasure of the Lord shall prosper in His hand. He shall see

04:57.380 --> 05:03.580
the travail of His soul, and shall be satisfied. By His knowledge shall My righteous servant

05:03.580 --> 05:10.440
justify many, for He shall bear their iniquities. Therefore will I divide Him a portion with the

05:10.440 --> 05:16.260
great, and He shall divide the spoil with the strong, because He hath poured out His soul unto

05:16.260 --> 05:22.780
death, and He was numbered with the transgressors, and He bare the sin of many and made intercession

05:22.780 --> 05:32.180
for the transgressors. Chapter 54 Sing, O barren, thou that didst not bear, break forth into singing

05:32.180 --> 05:38.760
and cry aloud, thou that didst not travail with child. For more are the children of the desolate

05:38.760 --> 05:45.220
than the children of the married wife, saith the Lord. Enlarge the place of thy tent, and let them

05:45.220 --> 05:51.800
stretch forth the curtains of thine habitations. Spare not, lengthen thy cords, and strengthen thy

05:51.800 --> 05:58.300
stakes. For thou shalt break forth on the right hand and on the left, and thy seed shall inherit

05:58.300 --> 06:05.900
the Gentiles, and make the desolate cities to be inhabited. Fear not, for thou shalt not be ashamed,

06:06.340 --> 06:12.460
neither be thou confounded, for thou shalt not be put to shame, for thou shalt forget the shame

06:12.460 --> 06:19.660
of thy youth, and shalt not remember the reproach of thy widowhood any more. For thy Maker is thine

06:19.660 --> 06:26.760
husband, the Lord of hosts is His name, and thy Redeemer, the Holy One of Israel, the God of the

06:26.760 --> 06:33.740
earth shall He be called. For the Lord hath called thee as a woman forsaken and grieved in spirit,

06:34.040 --> 06:41.940
and a wife of youth, when thou wast refused, saith thy God. For a small moment have I forsaken thee,

06:42.200 --> 06:48.940
but with great mercies will I gather thee. In a little wrath I hid my face from thee for a moment,

06:49.340 --> 06:54.940
but with everlasting kindness will I have mercy on thee, saith the Lord thy Redeemer.

06:55.660 --> 07:02.020
For this is as the waters of Noah unto me, for as I have sworn that the waters of Noah

07:02.020 --> 07:07.600
should no more go over the earth, so have I sworn that I would not be wroth with thee,

07:07.900 --> 07:14.700
nor rebuke thee. For the mountains shall depart and the hills be removed, but my kindness shall

07:14.700 --> 07:20.780
not depart from thee, neither shall the covenant of my peace be removed, saith the Lord that hath

07:20.780 --> 07:28.280
mercy on thee. O thou afflicted, tossed with tempest, and not comforted, behold, I will lay

07:28.280 --> 07:35.380
thy stones with fair colors and lay thy foundations with sapphires, and I will make thy windows of

07:35.380 --> 07:42.660
agates and thy gates of carbuncles and all thy borders of pleasant stones, and all thy children

07:42.660 --> 07:48.640
shall be taught of the Lord and great shall be the peace of thy children. In righteousness

07:48.640 --> 07:54.880
shalt thou be established, thou shalt be far from oppression, for thou shalt not fear,

07:55.180 --> 08:01.660
and from terror, for it shall not come near thee. Behold, they shall surely gather together,

08:01.800 --> 08:07.760
but not by me, whosoever shall gather together against thee shall fall for thy sake.

08:08.700 --> 08:14.660
Behold, I have created the smith that bloweth the coals in the fire and that bringeth forth an

08:14.660 --> 08:21.100
instrument for his work, and I have created the waster to destroy. No weapon that is formed

08:21.100 --> 08:26.160
against thee shall prosper, and every tongue that shall rise against thee in judgment,

08:26.580 --> 08:31.040
thou shalt condemn. This is the heritage of the servants of the Lord,

08:31.260 --> 08:34.640
and their righteousness is of me, saith the Lord.

